Class NetConn

java.lang.Object
  lib.CommonNetConn<java.lang.String>
      lib.NetConn
All Implemented Interfaces:
Config, CommonConfig, java.lang.Runnable
public class NetConn
extends CommonNetConn<java.lang.String>
implements java.lang.Runnable, Config

this class handles the network interaction for one frame. Essentially there are three states, active, connecting, and waiting. In active state, there is data on the way in, and we are either reading it or blocked waiting. In connecting state, we are trying to establish a connection and set up streams. If we fail, we set the connectionFailed flag. If we succeed, we enter active state. In waiting state, we've just started and we wait to be interrupted and told to connect.

setBufSize

public void setBufSize(int n)
Description copied from class: CommonNetConn
set the buffer size, which may be a limitation on the amount of data in a packet. There's no reason to low ball this number, but infinitely large packets are probably evidence of a runaway.
